Kehl: Dortmund warrant quarter-final place

Sebastian Kehl Captain Sebastian Kehl feels that Borussia Dortmund have earned their place in the quarter-finals of this season's UEFA Champions League.

Klopp: Kehl deserves win in 300th league match

Sebastian Kehl Jurgen Klopp wants Borussia Dortmund to mark Sebastian Kehlâ€™s 300th Bundesliga game with the 'gift' of victory.

Kehl not giving up on Bundesliga title

Sebastian Kehl Sebastian Kehl has refused to give up on the Bundesliga title, despite Borussia Dortmund sitting 20 points behind leaders Bayern Munich.

Kehl: Dortmund facing different Real Madrid

Sebastian Kehl Sebastian Kehl accepts Borussia Dortmund will be underdogs against Real Madrid, despite beating them in the UEFA Champions League last season.

Too early to write off Bayern, warns Dortmund legend Kehl

Sebastian Kehl Sebastian Kehl expects Bayern Munich to "fight back" from their indifferent start and establish themselves as title contenders.

Kehl: Dortmund denied Ballon d'Or nominations

Sebastian Kehl Borussia Dortmund captain Sebastian Kehl said his side deserved more recognition by the FIFA Ballon d'Or judges.

More injury worries for Dortmund after win

Borussia Dortmund Borussia Dortmund beat Steaua Bucharest 1-0 in a friendly on Saturday, but saw Sebastian Kehl and Kevin Grosskreutz forced off by injury.

Kehl outlines Dortmund's recovery plans

Sebastian Kehl Sebastian Kehl wants Borussia Dortmund to remember their qualities in order to improve on what has been a dire Bundesliga campaign so far.

Score to settle with Arsenal, says Klopp

Borussia Dortmund manager Jurgen Klopp has welcomed the chance to get revenge on Arsenal, after the two sides were pitted together in the Champions League draw.
